text: Elves are rad, I played an eladrin rogue, they have the feystep ability
what is the acronym DC I keep seeing
and a saving throw?
It just means difficulty check
So DC10 means you have to roll a 10 or higher to determine if you succeed
Saving throw is a roll to stop some ongoing effect
Like if you were poisoned you would roll a saving throw at the end of each of your turns to see if you stop the ongoing poison damage
